items.definition: Direction from which the most energetic waves are coming in the swell wave component of a sea.

prefLabel._value: Direction at spectral maximum of swell waves first component on the water body

items.definition: The average height of the highest one third of the wind sea waves, where the height is defined as the vertical distance from a wave trough to the following wave crest.

prefLabel._value: Significant height of wind sea waves on the water body

items.definition: Period of the highest wind sea wave peak analysed by spectral method.

prefLabel._value: Period at spectral maximum of wind sea waves on the water body

items.definition: Direction (related to true north) from which the peak period wind sea waves are coming from analysed by spectral method.

prefLabel._value: Direction at spectral maximum of wind sea waves on the water body

items.definition: The maximum period of the waves analysed by zero crossing method.

prefLabel._value: Maximum zero crossing period of waves on the water body

items.definition: The mean of the highest third of waves on the water body analysed by zero crossing method.

prefLabel._value: Average height of the highest 1/3rd of waves on the water body

items.definition: The period of the significant wave analysed by zero crossing method.

prefLabel._value: Average zero crossing period of waves on the water body

items.definition: The average period of the highest tenth of waves measured during a recording burst.

prefLabel._value: Average zero crossing period of the highest 1/10th waves on the water body

items.definition: Fourier Analysis on directional sea level elevation, also named 'Directional Spectral density' or 'Directional Power spectral density'.

prefLabel._value: Variance spectral density of waves on the water body

items.definition: Sea surface wave directional variance spectral density is the variance of the amplitude of the waves within given ranges of direction and wave frequency.

prefLabel._value: Directional variance spectral density of waves on the water body
